The article is a transcript of remarks made by Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau and US President Donald Trump during a meeting at the Fairmont Le Manoir Richelieu in Charlevoix, Canada. They discussed various issues including trade, growing the middle class, and the possibility of a new form of NAFTA agreement. They did not discuss Russia and there was mention of a joint statement. Trudeau stated that he is not disappointed that Trump is leaving early.